race.comment: Keep a close eye on the late betting moves. DONE LEAVY (8) won a Flemington jumpout and then missed a whisker at Swan Hill on debut. Has been kept up to the mark with a jumpout and stripping fitter can go one better for a top metro stable. TAN TAT DELIGHT (12) debuts for the Waller yard and has looked sharp in her leadups. Profiles well and a bold run is anticipated. KOKO (9) debuts and has also impressed at the jumpouts. Draws awkwardly but has the blinkers on and is likely to race well. VERY FAMOUS (14) debuts and has had a string of promising jumpouts. Egan sticks from the last three and the blinkers are on. She has to be considered as well.
